txt.en: 'That is all I have to tell for now, my friend.'
The Rangers of Ithilien then spoke to the strange Halflings.\n\nAnborn is telling you a tale of strange travellers in Ithilien. You should listen closely.
The Rangers of Ithilien were patrolling to the north-east of Henneth Ann√ªn.\n\nAnborn is telling you a tale of strange travellers in Ithilien. You should listen closely.
'I will not soon forget those Halflings, for they were bold to give Faramir such cheek!'
The Rangers of Ithilien spied the barren camp-site and moved to investigate.\n\nAnborn is telling you a tale of strange travellers in Ithilien. You should listen closely.
Anborn will not soon forget the doughty little Halflings who gave such cheek to his captain, Faramir.
'I discovered only a smouldering fire, and none nearby to tend it...'
'It was then two small creatures leapt from the brush and raised their weapons against us!'
Walk with the Rangers of Ithilien
